363 settlement is fair, adequate, reasonable, and in the public interest. Any disposition by the attorney
364 general shall provide compensation for reasonable attorneys’ fees and costs expended on behalf
365 of the relator in instituting the action.
366 (11) If the attorney general does not intervene in the action, the relator shall have the
